│ of the call will be within the half-open interval `[1,       │
│ 33)`.\n\nWhen the input `%x` is `0`, `ctpop(0)` is `0`. This │
│ violates the `range` promise. According to LLVM's semantics, │
│ a value that violates its `range` metadata becomes           │
│ `poison`.\n\n*   In the **source IR**, the expression is     │
