│ `call` to `@llvm.ctpop.i32` has `range(i32 1, 33)` metadata  │
│ attached. This metadata is a promise from the programmer (or │
│ a previous optimization pass) that the result of the call    │
│ will be within the half-open interval `[1, 33)`.             │
│                                                              │
│ When the input `%x` is `0`, `ctpop(0)` is `0`. This violates │
│ the `range` promise. According to LLVM's semantics, a value  │
│ that violates its `range` metadata becomes `poison`.         │
│                                                              │
