│ == 0), i1 true, i1 (poison == 1)`. Since the select          │
│ condition `(%x == 0)` is `true`, the result is `true`, and   │
│ the `poison` value is never evaluated.                       │
│ *   In the **transformed IR**, the expression is `poison <   │
│ 2`. Any operation on `poison` results in `poison`.           │
│                                                              │
│ Thus, the transformation incorrectly changes a well-defined  │
│ `true` result into `poison` for the input `x = 0`, as        │
│ correctly identified by `alive2`.                            │
