│ I will fix the bug in `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` where an        │
│ incorrect transformation occurs due to `range` metadata on a │
│ `ctpop` intrinsic. The optimization `(icmp eq ctpop(X) 1) |  │
│ (icmp eq X 0)` -> `(icmp ult ctpop(X) 2)` is invalid when    │
│ `ctpop(0)` produces a `poison` value because its result `0`  │
│ is outside the specified range.                              │
│                                                              │
│ My plan is to add a check within `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` to   │
│ detect this situation. Specifically, I will check if the     │
│ `ctpop` instruction is a `CallInst` with `range` metadata on │
│ its return value. If the range's lower bound is greater than │
│ 0, it means `ctpop(0)` would result in `poison`, making the  │
│ transformation unsafe. In this case, I will abort the        │
│ optimization.                                                │
│                                                              │
│ I will now implement this fix.                               │
│                                                              │
│ <tool_call>                                                  │
│ {                                                            │
│   "name": "edit",                                            │
│   "args": {                                                  │
│     "file":                                                  │
│ "llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp",   │
│     "old": "  Value *CtPop = Cmp0->getOperand(0);\n  if      │
│ (IsAnd && Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && Pred1 ==             │
│ ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)\n    return Builder.CreateICmpUGT(CtPop,  │
│ ConstantInt::get(CtPop->getType(), 1));\n  if (!IsAnd &&     │
│ Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)\n  │
│ return Builder.CreateICmpULT(CtPop,                          │
│ ConstantInt::get(CtPop->getType(), 2));",                    │
│     "new": "  Value *CtPop = Cmp0->getOperand(0);\n\n  if    │
│ (IsAnd && Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && Pred1 ==             │
│ ICmpInst::ICMP_NE)\n    return Builder.CreateICmpUGT(CtPop,  │
│ ConstantInt::get(CtPop->getType(), 1));\n\n  if (!IsAnd &&   │
│ Pred0 == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ && Pred1 == ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ)    │
│ {\n    // This transform is not safe if ctpop(0) is poison,  │
│ which can happen if\n    // the ctpop has a range metadata   │
