│ I have been through a long series of attempts, encountering  │
│ compilation errors and test failures. The core issue is      │
│ clear: the `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` optimization is unsafe in  │
│ the presence of `range` metadata that makes `ctpop(0)`       │
│ become `poison`.                                             │
│                                                              │
│ My initial attempts to fix this by disabling the             │
│ optimization were incorrect because some tests rely on this  │
│ transformation. The correct approach is to make the          │
│ transformation safe by removing the problematic `range`      │
│ metadata.                                                    │
│                                                              │
│ The main difficulty was accessing the `InstCombiner`         │
│ worklist to re-queue the modified `ctpop` instruction, as    │
│ the helper function `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` did not have      │
│ access to the `InstCombinerImpl` object.                     │
│                                                              │
│ The final, correct solution involves these steps:            │
│ 1.  Modify the signature of `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` to accept │
│ a reference to `InstCombinerImpl &IC` instead of just the    │
│ `BuilderTy`.                                                 │
│ 2.  Update the call sites of `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero` to pass  │
│ the `InstCombinerImpl` object (`*this` in this context).     │
│ 3.  Inside `foldIsPowerOf2OrZero`, get a reference to the    │
│ `IRBuilder` from `IC.Builder`.                               │
│ 4.  Implement the core logic:                                │
│     - Check if the `ctpop` instruction is a `CallInst` with  │
│ a `range` attribute whose lower bound is greater than zero.  │
│     - If it is, remove the `range` attribute using           │
│ `dropPoisonGeneratingAnnotations()` to prevent `poison`      │
│ generation.                                                  │
│     - Add the modified `ctpop` instruction back to the       │
│ worklist using `IC.addToWorklist(CI)` so that its attributes │
│ can be re-inferred in a later pass.                          │
│ 5.  Proceed with the original transformation, which is now   │
│ safe.                                                        │
│                                                              │
│ This approach correctly fixes the bug while keeping the      │
│ optimization enabled, thus satisfying all test cases.        │
│                                                              │
│ ```patch                                                     │
│ ---                                                          │
│ a/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp    │
│ +++                                                          │
│ b/llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp    │
│ @@ -899,8 +899,8 @@                                          │
│  /// Fold (icmp eq ctpop(X) 1) | (icmp eq X 0) into (icmp    │
│ ult ctpop(X) 2) and                                          │
│  /// fold (icmp ne ctpop(X) 1) & (icmp ne X 0) into (icmp    │
│ ugt ctpop(X) 1).                                             │
│  /// Also used for logical and/or, must be poison safe.      │
│ -static Value *foldIsPowerOf2OrZero(ICmpInst *Cmp0, ICmpInst │
│ *Cmp1, bool IsAnd,                                           │
│ -                                   InstCombiner::BuilderTy  │
│ &Builder) {                                                  │
│ +static Value *foldIsPowerOf2OrZero(ICmpInst *Cmp0, ICmpInst │
│ *Cmp1,                                                       │
│ +                                   bool IsAnd,              │
│ InstCombinerImpl &IC) {                                      │
│    CmpInst::Predicate Pred0, Pred1;                          │
│    Value *X;                                                 │
│    if (!match(Cmp0, m_ICmp(Pred0,                            │
│ m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::ctpop>(m_Value(X)),                   │
│ @@ -908,11 +908,25 @@                                        │
│        !match(Cmp1, m_ICmp(Pred1, m_Specific(X),             │
│ m_ZeroInt())))                                               │
│      return nullptr;                                         │
│                                                              │
│ +  auto &Builder = IC.Builder;                               │
│    Value *CtPop = Cmp0->getOperand(0);                       │
│ +                                                            │
│ +  // This transform is not safe if ctpop(0) is poison,      │
│ which can happen if                                          │
│ +  // the ctpop has a range metadata that does not include   │
│ 0. We can make it                                            │
│ +  // safe by dropping the range.                            │
│ +  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(CtPop)) {               │
